<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 6:43PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Washington and south central Iron Counties through 730 PM MDT...
At 642 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Harmony, or 21 miles southwest of Cedar City, moving southeast at
5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
New Harmony and Kolob Canyon.
This includes Interstate 15 between mile markers 38 and 44.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
